/- A closed loop in a graph is a sequence of vertices starting and ending at the same vertex, where consecutive vertices are adjacent.
A closed loop can be represented as a sequence of vertices v_0, v_1, ..., v_k such that v_0 = v_k and for all i < k, v_i is adjacent to v_{i+1} in the graph. -/
def ClosedLoopWalk (G : SimpleGraph V) := Σ u : V, G.LoopWalk u u

/-- A walk is closed if its start and end vertices are the same. -/
@[simp]
def IsClosed {u v : V} (_ : G.LoopWalk u v) : Prop := u = v

/-- Define the equivalence relation for closed loop walks. -/
