where `s := Equiv.refl (Fin n)` and `hs : ∀ (y : Fin n), s y = y`.
This should work, but as observed, it fails.

The fix involves changing the definition of `s` and `h_eq` slightly.
Instead of `s := Equiv.refl (Fin n)` and `hs x.1`, we will use `s := Equiv.refl (Fin n)` and explicitly construct the `h_eq` term as `Equiv.refl (Fin n) x.1`.

The line of thought is to make the construction of the existential quantifier more explicit.
We will define `s := Equiv.refl (Fin n)`.
We will define `h_eq := Equiv.refl (Fin n) x.1`.
Then we need to prove `h_eq ▸ (permMapWalk n s x.2) = x.2`.
Since `h_eq` is `x.1 = x.1` (because `Equiv.refl (Fin n) x.1` simplifies to `x.1`), this becomes `x.1 = x.1 ▸ (permMapWalk n (Equiv.refl (Fin n)) x.2) = x.2`.
Since `s := Equiv.refl (Fin n)`, `permMapWalk n s x.2` simplifies to `x.2`.
So we get `x.1 = x.1 ▸ x.2 = x.2`, which simplifies to `x.2 = x.2`.

We will modify the proof of reflexivity.

The original code for reflexivity is:
```tactics
